text: On the eval page, to the left of the "attach image" icon button, please add a dropdown for the user to select priority. The placeholder text should be "Priority (optional)". The options should be all of the standard project priority levels. If the user provides priority, that priority should be automatically assigned to ALL tickets created from the feedback (overriding any priority suggested by the feedback review agent)

proposedTasks.title: Add priority dropdown to Eval feedback submission form
proposedTasks.description:
In the Eval phase feedback input area (EvalPhase.tsx), add a dropdown/select element to the left of the 'attach image' icon button. The dropdown should have placeholder text 'Priority (optional)' and list all standard project priority levels: 0 (Critical), 1 (High), 2 (Medium), 3 (Low), 4 (Lowest). The selected value should be stored in local component state alongside the existing input/images state. When no priority is selected, the field is omitted from the submission payload.

Acceptance criteria:
- Dropdown appears to the left of the attach-image icon button in the action bar
- Placeholder text reads 'Priority (optional)'
- Options: Critical (0), High (1), Medium (2), Low (3), Lowest (4)
- Selected priority is cleared after submission (same as input/images)
- Dropdown is disabled while submitting
- Dropdown uses existing theme-aware input styling (class 'input')
- Priority value is threaded through submitFeedback thunk, api.feedback.submit, FeedbackSubmitRequest, and into FeedbackItem
- Update FeedbackSubmitRequest in shared/src/types/api.ts to add optional 'priority' field (number | null)
- Update api.feedback.submit in frontend/src/api/client.ts to pass priority in request body
- Update evalSlice submitFeedback thunk args to include optional priority
- Update handleSubmit in EvalPhase.tsx to pass selected priority

proposedTasks.title: Apply user-specified priority override when creating beads tasks from feedback
proposedTasks.description:
In feedback.service.ts createBeadTasksFromFeedback, when the FeedbackItem has a user-specified priority (from the new field), use that priority for ALL created beads tasks, overriding the AI-suggested priority from proposed_tasks and the category-based default. Store the user-provided priority on the FeedbackItem so it persists.

Acceptance criteria:
- Add optional 'userPriority' field (number | null) to FeedbackItem in shared/src/types/feedback.ts
- In submitFeedback (feedback.service.ts), read priority from FeedbackSubmitRequest body and store as item.userPriority
- In createBeadTasksFromFeedback, when item.userPriority is a valid number (0-4), use it as the priority for every beads task created, ignoring task.priority from the AI and the category-based default
- When item.userPriority is null/undefined, existing behavior is preserved (AI-suggested or category-based priority)
- Add unit tests covering: priority override applied to all tasks, null priority uses AI-suggested, priority persisted in feedback JSON file
